Write a static method named vowelCount that accepts a String as a parameter and produces and 
returns an array of integers representing the counts of each vowel in the String. 
The array returned by your method should hold 5 elements: the first is the count of As, the second 
is the count of Es, the third Is, the fourth Os, and the fifth Us. Assume that the string contains no uppercase letters.

For example, the call vowelCount("i think, therefore i am") should return the array {1, 3, 3, 1, 0}.



public int[] vowelCount(String s)
{
    int[] count = new int[5];
    
    for (int i = 0; i < s.length(); i++)
    {
        switch(s.charAt(i))
        {
            case 'a':
            count[0]++;
            break;
            
            case 'e':
            count[1]++;
            break;
            
            case 'i':
            count[2]++;
            break;
            
            case 'o':
            count[3]++;
            break;
            
            case 'u':
            count[4]++;
            break;
        }
    }
    
    return count;
}
